org.sbml.jsbml.validator.offline.constraints

Interface AnyConstraint<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractConstraint, CategoryConstraintGroup, ConstraintGroup, ValidationConstraint

    public interface AnyConstraint<T>
    Basic interface which must be implemented by every kind of constraint. A class which implements this interface should be able to validate a object from class T.
    Since:
    1.2
    Author:
    Roman

    • Method Detail

      • check

        boolean check(ValidationContext context,
              T object)
        Checks if the object conforms to the specific rule in the given context.

        If the rule behaves different for each level/version, the level and version of the context will be used.

        Parameters:
        context - the validation context
        object - the object to validate
        Returns:
        false if the object does not respect the constraint

      • getErrorCode

        int getErrorCode()
        Returns the error code from this constraint.

        In the default case this should be an error code which is defined in the SBML specifications.

        Returns:
        the error code from this constraint.
